---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'June 30, 2026';
const contactEmail = 'support@pixanovalabs.com';
---

<Layout
  title="Delete your Herald account"
  description="How to request deletion of your Herald account and the data associated with it."
>
  <section class="policy">
    <div class="container policy__inner">
      <header class="policy__head">
        <div class="label">Account</div>
        <h1 class="policy__title">Delete your Herald account</h1>
        <p class="policy__updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </header>

      <div class="policy__intro card">
        <p>
          Herald is developed by <strong>Pixa Nova Labs</strong>. Signing in to Herald is optional.
          If you signed in with a Google account, this page explains how to delete your account and
          the data linked to it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="policy__body">
        <h2>How to request deletion</h2>
        <p>
          Email <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a> from the Google account email
          you use to sign in to Herald, with the subject <strong>"Delete my account"</strong>. So we
          can find the right account, please send it from that same email address.
        </p>
        <p>
          We will confirm and complete the deletion within <strong>30 days</strong>.
        </p>

        <h2>What gets deleted</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Your account's <strong>practice history</strong> stored in the cloud (which days you
            practised, which pages, and your scores) and your account record.
          </li>
          <li>
            The <strong>sign-in information</strong> we received from Google (your name, email, and
            user ID).
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What is already on your device, not our servers</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Your <strong>books and their text, local scores, and settings</strong> are stored only
            on your phone. They are removed when you clear the app's data or uninstall the app, and
            are not held on our servers.
          </li>
          <li>
            The app's <strong>anonymous daily-usage counter</strong> is not tied to your account and
            automatically expires after about two days.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          If you have any questions, contact us at
          <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .policy {
    padding-block: var(--space-16) var(--space-20);
    background-color: var(--color-surface);
  }

  .policy__inner {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .policy__head {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .policy__title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--size-h1);
    font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    line-height: var(--lh-heading);
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  .policy__updated {
    color: var(--color-secondary);
    font-size: var(--size-sm);
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }

  .policy__intro {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    background-color: var(--color-neutral);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
    line-height: var(--lh-body);
  }

  .policy__body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--size-h2);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-top: var(--space-10);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .policy__body p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    line-height: var(--lh-body);
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .policy__body ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .policy__body li {
    line-height: var(--lh-body);
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .policy__body a {
    color: var(--color-tertiary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .policy__body a:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }
</style>
